main event: Observers reported an oval-shaped object with a bright, bluish glow in Willsboro, New York on September 8, 1966.
interesting points: The object was heard upon arrival and departure., The sighting lasted for approximately 30 minutes., Witnesses reported a buzzing, whirring sound coming from the object., Witness Elizabeth Decker was accompanied by three others who also saw the object., The object was described as dull silver or gray in color and appeared to fade away into the sky or fog.
sighted object: oval-shaped object with a bright, bluish glow
witness description: Elizabeth Decker and three other unnamed witnesses
